Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add garlic and scallion whites; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30-45%seconds}.

Add @white rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, trim and quarter @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1/4-inch-thick pieces.

Drain and rinse @black beans{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add zucchini and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate. Wipe out pan.

Pat chicken cutlets dry with paper towels and season all over with @harissa powder{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> Be sure to measure the harissa powder—we sent more!

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for zucchini over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} and let rest at least ~{3%minutes}. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

While chicken cooks, in a #small bowl{}, whisk @BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon}, @honey{2%teaspoon}, 1 TBSP water, 1 tsp harissa powder, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{} to combine.

> Save remaining harissa powder for another use.

In pan used for chicken, bring honey BBQ mixture and 1/4 cup water to a simmer over medium heat. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> If glaze seems too thick, add more water 1 tsp at a time.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%TBSP} until melted. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in zucchini and beans. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide rice between plates. Top with chicken. Drizzle honey BBQ sauce over chicken; top with scallion greens. Serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.